        "text": "<@UC2A2ARPT> it's based on the same optimizer, but with one major tweak. If you run the vanilla Penrose optimizer, shapes that you are not interacting with tend to jump disconcertingly. We add what's called a \"lasso term\" so shape continuity is preserved during interaction.",
